keyFacts: The FBI's West Palm Beach office was billed by Sprint for investigative services in 2006.
The invoice is tied to Sprint Case #2006-149246, indicating an active investigation requiring phone record subpoena compliance.
The total amount due was $205.00 for a flat fee and detailed report services.
This document shows the FBI was incurring expenses for telecom records as part of an investigation in late 2006.
The billing address is the FBI's West Palm Beach field office, which was involved in the Epstein investigation.
